// MARK: - Region Detail — Sorth Risk Briefing

"region.south.riskBriefing" = "The South moves fast and forgives slow.\nRain turns streets into rivers in minutes. Heat lingers long after the flood drains. The people who thrive here learned to read the city the way sailors read weather — not by waiting for warnings, but by knowing what comes next.";

"region.south.sections.1.title" = "A CITY BUILT UPWARD, NOT OUTWARD";
"region.south.sections.1.content" = "Saigon stacks life vertically. High floors, narrow stairwells, lobbies lined with motorbikes, balconies wrapped in iron.\nPeople who belong here know their building the way they know their own kitchen.\nEvery exit, every shortcut.";
"region.south.sections.1.subtitle" = "Know two ways out of anywhere you sleep.";

"region.south.sections.2.title" = "WHEN THOUSANDS MOVE AS ONE";
"region.south.sections.2.content" = "Saigon knows how to celebrate. Countdown nights, street festivals, live events.\nThe city fills every open space with people and sound.\nThe ones who move through crowds well are not anxious.";
"region.south.sections.2.subtitle" = "Know where the exits are, and stay near the edge";

"region.south.sections.3.title" = "THE SECOND WAVE COMES QUIET";
"region.south.sections.3.content" = "Floodwater drains,\nDengue, skin infections, heat exhaustion,\n These arrive after the rain stops, when everyone has already relaxed.";
"region.sorth.sections.3.subtitle" = "The locals live by the calendar. You should too.";

"region.south.sections.4.title" = "THE NEIGHBORHOOD MOVES FIRST";
"region.south.sections.4.content" = "Official help follows.\nThe first response is always a neighbor at your door, a rider shouting through the street, youth volunteers moving before anyone gives the order.";
"region.sorth.sections.4.subtitle" = "Don't hide at home, the neighbors are the best rescuers";


// MARK: - Region Detail — Central Risk Briefing

"region.central.riskBriefing" = "The Central coast lives between the sea and the mountains.\nTyphoons arrive from one side, landslides answer from the other.\nThe towns in between have weathered this longer than anyone alive.\nWhat they know is not fear, it is timing.";

"region.central.sections.1.title" = "WHERE THE SEA MEETS THE MOUNTAIN";
"region.central.sections.1.content" = "From the beach to the mountain pass is one step.\nAncient towns sit in wooden alleyways built for beauty.\nWhen the river rises, it does not climb slowly. \nUpstream dams release water during the peak of a storm, and the surge arrives faster than any forecast.";
"region.central.sections.1.subtitle" = "In the Central, the geography decides the timeline.";

"region.central.sections.2.title" = "THE ONES WHO STAY BEHIND";
"region.central.sections.2.content" = "The loudspeaker says evacuate. But the house holds everything you own.\nEvery storm, someone decides to stay, to guard the furniture, the workstation, the livestock. \nThe flood does not negotiate with reasons.\nThe people who have done this before know what can be replaced and what cannot.";
"region.central.sections.2.subtitle" = "Nothing you own is worth what happens if you stay.";

"region.central.sections.3.title" = "THE ROAD CUTS BEFORE THE STORM ENDS";
"region.central.sections.3.content" = "When the rain stops, the roads are already gone. \nSupply trucks cannot reach for days. Relief points fill with hundreds of families at once.\nThe heat that follows is different from the storm.\nThe prepared ones stocked before the sky changed.";
"region.central.sections.3.subtitle" = "In the Central, isolation comes before recovery.";

"region.central.sections.4.title" = "THE WARNING TRAVELS BY VOICE";
"region.central.sections.4.content" = "Loudspeakers, flags, messengers running mountain roads. The network of elders, fishermen, and youth groups reaches every house before any app does.\nThe ones who listened are the ones who moved.";
"region.central.sections.4.subtitle" = "Follow the voice";


// MARK: - Region Detail — Nouth Risk Briefing

"region.north.riskBriefing" = "The North is old and does not explain itself.\nMountains shift without warning. Rivers that were calm at dawn swallow roads by noon. The cold settles in for months. The people here plan ahead not out of worry, but because the land taught them what happens when you don't.";

"region.north.sections.1.title" = "THE LAND MOVES ON ITS OWN SCHEDULE";
"region.north.sections.1.content" = "Mountain passes connect everything — and disappear in hours. Flash floods funnel through narrow valleys with a speed flat-landers never expect.\nLandslides caused seventy-nine percent of deaths during Typhoon Yagi. The slopes do not crack loudly before they go.\nThe people who travel these roads know the sky, the soil, and when to turn back.";
"region.north.sections.1.subtitle" = "Trust the mountain less after rain.";

"region.north.sections.2.title" = "HUMIDITY BURNS, COLD TRAPS";
"region.north.sections.2.content" = "Nồm season fills the walls with water. Moisture crawls inside wiring and appliances until something sparks.\nIn winter, families seal every window and light coal braziers for warmth. The carbon monoxide has no smell.\nThe ones who last through Northern seasons respect what they cannot see.";
"region.north.sections.2.subtitle" = "The weather inside the house is just as important.";

"region.north.sections.3.title" = "WHEN THE PASS CLOSES, YOU ARE ALONE";
"region.north.sections.3.content" = "One blocked road isolates an entire district. Supplies stop. Communication drops. Mountain communities have lived with this rhythm for generations.\nThey stock fuel, rice, and medicine before the season turns. By the time outsiders notice, the prepared ones are already settled in.";
"region.north.sections.3.subtitle" = "The locals live by the calendar. You should too.";

"region.north.sections.4.title" = "THE CIRCLE COMES BEFORE THE STATE";
"region.north.sections.4.content" = "Village committees, rapid-response teams, neighbors with rope — rescue in the North starts local.\nThey string lines across rivers, dig through landslides by hand, and share fire before any vehicle can reach them.\nThe ones who made it were already inside the circle.";
"region.north.sections.4.subtitle" = "Join early. The door closes when the storm hits.";


